Risk Assessment: 

Bouncing superbouncy balls under coffee tables and rolling them against
walls.

Risks +
1. Minimal risk of injury from balls if thrown by children +
2. Loose balls could pose a trip hazard

Control Measures: +
1. Keep hold of the balls not being used. Recover balls if being used
inappropriately. +
2. Don't set up the experiment in a thoroughfare where the balls could
be a trip hazard. If a ball rolls into thoroughfare, retrieve it
immediately.

In case of accident: +
In case of injury, call a first aider.

